"title": "4945: history",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4945: history",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>In Scripture, more than a record of and reflection on past events, but a process under God's control which has as its goal the eventual fulfilment of his purposes and through which he makes himself known. The goal of history is realised in Jesus Christ, through whom the age of salvation is inaugurated. Both the OT and NT point to the importance of faith rooted in historical events.</p>\n<h2>God is active in history</h2>\n<h3>God's control over historical events</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan2:21\">DAN 2:21</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:26\">ACT 17:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen45:5-Gen45:8\">GEN 45:5–45:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs12:15\">1KI 12:15</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr10:15\">2CH 10:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan4:25\">DAN 4:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan7:25\">DAN 7:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos9:7\">AMO 9:7</a></p>\n<h3>God's saving purposes worked out through history</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:11\">EPH 1:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa14:24-Isa14:27\">ISA 14:24–14:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa37:26\">ISA 37:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa41:4\">ISA 41:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa46:10-Isa46:11\">ISA 46:10–46:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:7\">ACT 1:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:23\">ACT 2:23</a></p>\n<h2>God is known through his people's history</h2>\n<h3>God is known to his people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa46:9\">ISA 46:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod10:2\">EXO 10:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut4:32-Deut4:35\">DEU 4:32–4:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps77:11-Ps77:15\">PSA 77:11–77:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa43:10-Isa43:13\">ISA 43:10–43:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa44:6-Isa44:8\">ISA 44:6–44:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic6:5\">MIC 6:5</a></p>\n<h3>God is revealed to the nations</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps126:2\">PSA 126:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:56-1Kgs8:60\">1KI 8:56–8:60</a></p>\n<h2>The Israelites were called to remember their history</h2>\n<h3>The past was recalled in festivals</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:42-Lev23:43\">LEV 23:42–23:43</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut16:1-Deut16:6\">DEU 16:1–16:6</a></p>\n<h3>The past was recounted to successive generations</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps78:2-Ps78:7\">PSA 78:2–78:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:7-Deut32:9\">DEU 32:7–32:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:13\">JDG 6:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps44:1-Ps44:3\">PSA 44:1–44:3</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ as the centre of the history of salvation</h2>\n<h3>He is its beginning and end</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:13\">REV 22:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:8\">REV 1:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:17\">REV 1:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:8\">REV 2:8</a></p>\n<h3>God's saving purposes in history fulfilled in Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:9-Eph1:10\">EPH 1:9–1:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:6\">ROM 5:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:4\">GAL 4:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:17\">COL 1:17</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ inaugurates God's new age</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:18\">COL 1:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan7:13-Dan7:14\">DAN 7:13–7:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:15\">MRK 1:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:28\">MAT 12:28</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:20\">LUK 11:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:7\">EPH 2:7</a></p>\n<h2>The Christian faith is based on the historical facts of salvation</h2>\n<h3>Testimony passed on by eye-witnesses</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:1-Luke1:4\">LUK 1:1–1:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:3\">HEB 2:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:1\">1PE 5:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet1:16\">2PE 1:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John1:1-1John1:3\">1JN 1:1–1:3</a></p>\n<h3>Remembering Jesus Christ's death</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:23-1Cor11:25\">1CO 11:23–11:25</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:19-Luke22:20\">LUK 22:19–22:20</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's resurrection as historical fact</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:3\">ACT 1:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:1-Luke24:3\">LUK 24:1–24:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:39\">LUK 24:39</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:27\">JHN 20:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:3-1Cor15:8\">1CO 15:3–15:8</a></p>\n<h3>Historical references in the NT</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:1-Luke1:2\">LUK 1:1–1:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt2:1\">MAT 2:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:1-Luke3:2\">LUK 3:1–3:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:3-Matt14:4\">MAT 14:3–14:4</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:17-Mark6:18\">MRK 6:17–6:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:37\">ACT 5:37</a></p>\n<h2>Landmarks in salvation history</h2>\n<h3>The creation</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:1\">GEN 1:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:7\">GEN 2:7</a></p>\n<h3>The fall</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:6-Gen3:7\">GEN 3:6–3:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:12\">ROM 5:12</a></p>\n<h3>The call of Abraham</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen12:1-Gen12:3\">GEN 12:1–12:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:8\">HEB 11:8</a></p>\n<h3>The exodus from Egypt</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod13:3\">EXO 13:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod19:4-Exod19:6\">EXO 19:4–19:6</a></p>\n<h3>The birth of Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:14\">JHN 1:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:1-Heb1:2\">HEB 1:1–1:2</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's death and resurrection</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:3-1Cor15:4\">1CO 15:3–15:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:6-Phil2:11\">PHP 2:6–2:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:3-Heb1:4\">HEB 1:3–1:4</a></p>",
